@startuml
title Autoscaling Strategy - PSTA Platform

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Digital Channels\n(Mobile / Web / APIs)" as Channels

rectangle "Transaction Load" as Load

cloud "Prometheus Metrics" as Prometheus

cloud "Kafka Topics" as Kafka

component "Horizontal Pod Autoscaler\n(HPA)" as HPA

component "KEDA\n(Event Driven Autoscaling)" as KEDA

component "Cluster Autoscaler" as CA

frame "AWS EKS Cluster" {

    package "Risk Assessment Service" {

        component "Pod-1" as Risk1
        component "Pod-2" as Risk2
        component "Pod-N" as RiskN
    }

    package "Transaction Decision Service" {

        component "Pod-1" as Decision1
        component "Pod-2" as Decision2
        component "Pod-N" as DecisionN
    }

    package "Adaptive Authentication Service" {

        component "Pod-1" as Auth1
        component "Pod-2" as Auth2
        component "Pod-N" as AuthN
    }

    package "Account Protection Service" {

        component "Pod-1" as Protect1
        component "Pod-2" as Protect2
        component "Pod-N" as ProtectN
    }

    package "Audit Service" {

        component "Pod-1" as Audit1
        component "Pod-2" as Audit2
        component "Pod-N" as AuditN
    }
}

node "Worker Node A" as NodeA
node "Worker Node B" as NodeB
node "Worker Node N" as NodeN

Channels --> Load

Load --> Risk1
Load --> Decision1
Load --> Auth1

Risk1 --> Kafka
Decision1 --> Kafka
Protect1 --> Kafka
Audit1 --> Kafka

Prometheus --> HPA : CPU\nMemory\nTPS

Kafka --> KEDA : Consumer Lag\nPending Messages

HPA --> RiskN : Scale Pods
HPA --> DecisionN : Scale Pods
HPA --> AuthN : Scale Pods

KEDA --> RiskN : Scale Consumers
KEDA --> ProtectN : Scale Consumers
KEDA --> AuditN : Scale Consumers

RiskN --> NodeA
DecisionN --> NodeB
AuthN --> NodeN
ProtectN --> NodeA
AuditN --> NodeB

HPA --> CA : More Pods Needed
KEDA --> CA : More Pods Needed

CA --> NodeN : Add Worker Nodes

note right of HPA

Metrics Based Scaling

CPU > 70%

Memory > 75%

TPS Threshold

end note

note right of KEDA

Event Driven Scaling

Kafka Lag

Transaction Volume

Authentication Events

Fraud Events

end note

note right of CA

Infrastructure Scaling

Add Nodes

Remove Nodes

Based on Scheduling Capacity

end note

note bottom

Scaling Strategy

Level 1

Pods Scale Out

(HPA / KEDA)

↓

Level 2

Nodes Scale Out

(Cluster Autoscaler)

↓

Level 3

Multi-AZ Distribution

Benefits

✓ Elastic Capacity

✓ Cost Optimization

✓ Event-Driven Scaling

✓ High Availability

✓ Kafka Consumer Scaling

end note
@enduml